Name: Commemorative Marker of Re-Interred Bodies Buried in City Hall Park
Caption: City Hall Park
Description: Geo coordinates for the commemorative marker located in the northeast corner of City Hall Park, which notes that bodies were disturbed during renovations to buidlings and the area; disturbed bodies were reinterred in this section of the park, and a commemorative marker was placed to mark the location, in 2010.
Citation: Gertner, Larry. “Interment Site Historical Marker.” The Historical Marker Database, 7 Mar. 2019, https://www.hmdb.org/m.asp?m=130550. Accessed 18 Mar. 2021.
